<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">April 14, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-april-14-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-101491 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/220px-TheGreatGatsby_1925jacket-e1744400231762-150x150.jpeg" alt="F. Scott Fitzgerald, The Great Gatsby" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.publicbooks.org/gatsby-100-american-classrooms-american-dreams/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">On the study of </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">The Great Gatsby </span></i><span style="font-weight: 400">in American high schools</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/features/a64456914/maine-white-supremacy/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mira Ptacin on the illusion of safety and white supremacist violence</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/books/642259/booktok-romantasy-men" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The world of online men cashing in on romantasy</span></a></li>
</ul>
